cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on developing an embodied system using social robotics to carry out neuropsychological tests. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The system will use methods from machine learning to detect early signs of dementia. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The interaction between the system and patients will be developed using a participatory design approach. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper explicitly mentions the use of machine learning methods. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): Although not as prominent as the other categories, the paper mentions the use of recorded clinician-patient interactions, which could involve natural language processing techniques.
